Add footer. 

1. Create a new branch called nayana/footer from main branch main.
    ---> Ans: * Before creating new branch first we have to switch in to main brabch <git checkout main>this command get us exsisting branch (nayana/ navigationbar) to main branch
              * next to create new branch <git checkout -b nayana/footer>this command get us new branch called nayana/footer
    
2. Create a new .js file called Footer.js inside src folder  // this file used to create a react component
    ---> Ans: inside the src folder we have to create new file called --Footer.js--firstletter always should be in capital letter that seems to be a component <right click on src folder--new file--Footer.js>

3. Create a new .css file called Footer.css inside src folder 
    ---> Ans: inside the src folder we have to create new file called --Footer.css--firstletter always should be in      capital letter that seems to be a component <right click on src folder--new file--Footer.css>


4. Create a function called Footer inside Footer.js file just take reference from App.js file
    ---> Ans: inside the Footer.js file we have to write the function like
    <function Footer()>

5. Imort Footer.css file inside Footer.js file 
    ---> Ans: inside the Footer.js file we have to import library called
    <import './Footer.css';>
              inside the App.js file we have to import library called
    <import Footer from './footer.js';>

    App.js file

import logo from './logo.svg';
import './App.css';
import Footer from './Footer';

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="#services">Services</a></li>
      <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
   </ul>
   <Footer />
    </div>
  );
}
 
 
 6. Add footer html code inside Footer.js file // just use google it or use chat gpt for this
    ---> Ans: inside Footer.js file 
 Footer.js
 
import logo from './logo.svg';
